node.title: Victoria investigating seven COVID cases linked to possible Omicron exposure
node.description: Genomic sequencing is underway for around 30 COVID-positive people who are suspected to have the Omicron variant of the virus, as Victoria records another 1,622 new infections and nine deaths.

node.title: Underperforming super funds named and shamed by regulator
node.description: Super fund members are being urged to consider switching funds as the regulator warns the industry they need to lift their game on fees and investment performance, with new data showing more funds are failing to stack up.

node.title: Man who kidnapped toddler in 'horrendously misplaced' adoption plot released after time served
node.description: Olando Aleki, 31, is sentenced to three years in jail after pleading guilty to child stealing and entering a dwelling with intent. He is being released from jail after time served, and could now face deportation.

node.title: SA records 24 new COVID-19 cases, including four of the Omicron variant
node.description: South Australia records 24 new cases of COVID-19 as six new close contact exposure sites are identified, including prominent Adelaide CBD restaurants.

node.title: Reserve Bank bond-buying to end in May unless economy falters, Lowe says
node.description: The Reserve Bank governor lays out the options for its stimulus programs next year, with the outcome depending largely on the Omicron outbreak.

node.title: 'The dog is dead': Encrypted texts that organised Sydney underworld hit revealed for first time
node.description: Sydney gangster Pasquale Barbaro was killed in 2016. After three secret trials, the details of his underworld execution can finally be revealed.

node.title: MYEFO is forecasting a long-awaited rise in wages, but it doesn't mean it will happen
node.description: It's tough making predictions, especially about the future and even more so during a pandemic. But Josh Frydenberg and Treasury have had another crack in MYEFO, writes Ian Verrender.

node.title: Strong winds and tornadoes sweep through Great Plains and Midwest
node.description: The National Weather Service said there have been 13 tornado reports in the Plains states, scattered through eastern Nebraska and Iowa.

node.title: 2 Children Killed After Falling From Inflatable Castle in Tasmania
node.description: The students fell 33 feet from a jumping castle that was lifted into the air by a gust of wind, the authorities said. Several others were critically injured.

node.title: Stunning Video Shows Blinding Dust Storm in Kansas as Severe Weather Wallops Plains
node.description: The state is experiencing concurrent wildfires, windstorms and dust storms that have demolished buildings and caused power outages and road closures.

node.title: Police still negotiating with activists shovelling coal off Queensland freight train
node.description: One protester has been arrested over the protest, which began yesterday afternoon.

node.title: Covid-19: Omicron spreading at unprecedented rate - WHO
node.description: The new coronavirus variant Omicron is spreading across the globe at an unprecedented rate, the World Health Organisation (WHO) has warned.

node.title: Covid-19: Medsafe gives provisional approval for Pfizer vaccine for children
node.description: Medsafe has granted provisional approval for the Pfizer Covid-19 vaccine for children aged 5 to 11 years old.

node.title: Reddit takes first official step toward going public.
node.description: The company announced it had confidentially filed paperwork for an I.P.O., but without disclosing financial details.

node.title: Social Media Helps Sounds of Endangered Birds Soar to No. 5 on the Australian Music Charts
node.description: "This album is a very special record with some rare recordings," said BirdLife Australia CEO Paul Sullivan.

node.title: Congress Sends Biden $768B Defense Bill With Plans for New War on Terror Memorial in D.C.
node.description: The $768 billion annual defense bill also includes changes to how sexual assault cases are handled in the military, and proposals for a war on terror memorial.

node.title: Pennsylvania Woman Sentenced to Consecutive Life Terms After Killing Her Kids With Shotgun

node.title: Sheriff Accused of Threatening Church Youth Group With Gun After They Left Thank-You Note
node.description: On Tuesday, Craig Rowland was charged with aggravated battery, aggravated assault, and misdemeanor exhibition of a gun by the Idaho Attorney General's Office.

node.title: Man who raped woman he found on Melbourne footpath jailed for 'shameful' crime
node.description: Harley Palise will spend at least four years in jail for raping a woman he and another man found slumped on a footpath in Carlton.

node.title: Ashes battle resumes

node.title: Covid-19 milestone: 90pc of eligible New Zealanders are now fully vaccinated
node.description: Ninety percent of eligible New Zealanders are now fully vaccinated, with the official count through overnight, Covid-19 Response Minister Chris Hipkins says.

node.title: Torrential rain: Flooding, evacuations and road closures in Canterbury and Wellington

node.title: C.D.C. panel will discuss blood clot risk linked to J.&J.’s vaccine.
node.description: On Thursday, agency advisers will review updated figures showing roughly nine deaths from the rare disorder, according to a federal official.

node.title: Grayden Lane Denham Convicted of Killing Grandparents, Sister, 3-Month-Old Nephew
node.description: On Tuesday, a Platte County, Missouri, jury found Denham guilty of four counts of first-degree murder, four counts of armed criminal action and other crimes.

node.title: Influx From Infrastructure Bill Expected to Help Amtrak's Worn Northeast Corridor

node.title: Massive Los Angeles School District Pushes Back Deadline For Student Vaccination Mandate

node.title: Car crashes through walls of Melbourne shopping centre, hitting six people

node.title: 'End of my tether': Northland's tourism industry fears for future in traffic light red

node.title: All Blacks hooker Codie Taylor re-signs ahead of 2023 World Cup
